May l?
Please.

243
00:34:47,618 --> 00:34:50,052
It is very beautiful.

244
00:34:50,254 --> 00:34:53,553
It is a very beautiful color.

245
00:34:53,758 --> 00:35:01,221
Perhaps you'll see the color better
if you took off your glasses.

246
00:35:04,102 --> 00:35:06,900
Are you enjoying Venice?

247
00:35:08,106 --> 00:35:12,600
Yes, I have, very much. Thank you.

248
00:35:12,810 --> 00:35:15,244
It is heart of Venice to catch some.

249
00:35:15,446 --> 00:35:20,907
Yes, I felt that.
You feel Venice. That's a wonderful feeling.

250
00:35:23,454 --> 00:35:26,890
Have you a pair? Two?

251
00:35:27,091 --> 00:35:31,551
No, I'm sorry.
This is the only one I have.

252
00:35:31,929 --> 00:35:36,889
How much did you say it was?
To you, 1 0,000 liras. It is genuine.

253
00:35:37,101 --> 00:35:40,332
Wrap it up. I'll take it.

254
00:35:40,538 --> 00:35:45,475
You take it? At this price?
That is the price isn't it?

255
00:35:45,676 --> 00:35:49,772
Excuse me, Miss.
Have you bought many things in ltaly?

256
00:35:49,914 --> 00:35:53,782
No, I havn't. This is the first time.
I just came yesterday.

257
00:35:53,985 --> 00:35:58,718
Forgive me. But in ltaly,
you must not say so quick" I take it."

258
00:35:58,923 --> 00:36:01,153
You must bargain.
Why?

259
00:36:01,359 --> 00:36:04,294
It is a part of buying and selling.

260
00:36:04,495 --> 00:36:07,362
I'll give it you for 8,700 liras.

261
00:36:07,565 --> 00:36:09,829
No, you don't.
Why?

262
00:36:10,034 --> 00:36:12,025
Because it's not fair.
But I want to.

263
00:36:12,236 --> 00:36:14,534
Yes, but I bought it for 1 0,000 lira.

264
00:36:14,739 --> 00:36:18,607
Then I give it to you for
8,700 lira in honor of your first

265
00:36:18,809 --> 00:36:21,903
buying in ltaly.

266
00:36:22,113 --> 00:36:25,549
Well, I give in. I mean, I give up.

267
00:36:25,750 --> 00:36:27,513
Thank you.
Very good.

268
00:36:27,718 --> 00:36:32,917
I'll wrap it up.
You'll wrap it up.

269
00:36:33,124 --> 00:36:36,093
Thank you.

270
00:36:38,129 --> 00:36:40,620
Will you be staying long in Venice?

271
00:36:40,831 --> 00:36:45,291
That depends.
I mean...I feel if I can stay forever.

272
00:36:46,470 --> 00:36:50,531
That is a fact what it says.

273
00:36:50,741 --> 00:36:53,642
By the way, if it were possible
to get another goblet,

274
00:36:53,844 --> 00:36:56,779
Would you wish to have it?

275
00:36:56,981 --> 00:37:01,441
Oh, yes.
I think it is possible I may find one.

276
00:37:01,919 --> 00:37:03,819
Perhaps you would call again?

277
00:37:04,021 --> 00:37:06,012
Or perhaps I could send it to your hotel?

278
00:37:06,224 --> 00:37:08,192
Where you're staying?
In Venice.

279
00:37:08,392 --> 00:37:12,260
What?
I mean, in Pensioni Fiorini.

280
00:37:12,463 --> 00:37:14,590
Oh, yes.

281
00:37:14,799 --> 00:37:18,667
Thank you.
Hope to see you again.

282
00:37:18,869 --> 00:37:21,838
Thank you.

283
00:37:25,176 --> 00:37:27,701
Thank you.

284
00:37:27,912 --> 00:37:31,279
Thank you.
Your glasses.

285
00:37:31,482 --> 00:37:34,144
You'll wear it or carry it?

286
00:37:34,352 --> 00:37:37,116
Carry them. Thank you.

287
00:37:37,321 --> 00:37:41,781
Good-by.
Good-by.

288
00:37:53,804 --> 00:37:56,500
Dearest Ben and Betty:
Venice is as unbelievable as fairy tale,

289
00:37:56,707 --> 00:38:01,041
How I wish you're here.

290
00:38:01,245 --> 00:38:07,206
This time, we'll be a quartet.

291
00:38:08,019 --> 00:38:13,980
Mio Amico has silver-gray hair.

292
00:38:16,694 --> 00:38:18,924
Cookie, you're a very pretty girl.

293
00:38:19,130 --> 00:38:20,722
Yes. I know.

294
00:38:20,931 --> 00:38:24,094
But I'm not interested
in looking like the women in paintings.

295
00:38:24,302 --> 00:38:26,429
You are.
C'mon.

296
00:38:26,637 --> 00:38:28,798
No, You are.

297
00:38:29,006 --> 00:38:33,238
What's the matter?
Nothing.

298
00:38:33,444 --> 00:38:38,882
Someday when you're not so busy,
how about you showing me the town.

299
00:38:39,083 --> 00:38:41,551
I've been hurrying for ten minutes.

300
00:38:41,752 --> 00:38:42,878
I'll call a boat.
Ok.

301
00:38:43,087 --> 00:38:46,523
We could go swimming.
Sure.

302
00:38:46,724 --> 00:38:51,525
We're out to Harry's bar.
The book says that's a must.

303
00:38:51,729 --> 00:38:53,822
Ok.

304
00:38:54,031 --> 00:38:56,761
Will you excuse us?
Sure. Have fun.

305
00:38:56,967 --> 00:38:58,798
Be seeing you.
Yes.

306
00:38:59,003 --> 00:39:03,463
Bye.
Bye.

307
00:39:07,578 --> 00:39:10,979
Hey! Why don't l
give Harry his big break tonight.

308
00:39:11,015 --> 00:39:14,246
Do you mind if I come along with you?
I always buy my guy a drink.

309
00:39:14,452 --> 00:39:16,886
Sure.
We'll meet some people.

310
00:39:17,088 --> 00:39:20,922
How about bring them, too?
Are there too many of them?

311
00:39:21,125 --> 00:39:24,219
Just another couple.
We're going on to dinner together.

312
00:39:24,428 --> 00:39:27,329
Sure. Have fun.

313
00:39:27,531 --> 00:39:31,991
Oh, Eddie.
Miss. Hudson.

314
00:40:53,984 --> 00:40:56,953
Coffee.

315
00:42:34,218 --> 00:42:38,678
Good evening.
Good evening.

316
00:44:15,452 --> 00:44:18,114
You frightened me.
How did you know I was here?

317
00:44:18,322 --> 00:44:21,291
(ltalian.)

318
00:44:24,161 --> 00:44:27,096
Oh, I like it this way.

319
00:44:27,297 --> 00:44:29,595
Lady, you got any brothers and sisters?

320
00:44:29,800 --> 00:44:31,324
Three, cookie.

321
00:44:31,535 --> 00:44:37,474
You very lucky. Three brothers
and sisters. I got three of these.

322
00:44:37,675 --> 00:44:41,076
Presents. Souvenirs of ltaly.

323
00:44:41,278 --> 00:44:43,508
You're impossible.

324
00:44:43,714 --> 00:44:47,810
Ok. Ok.
Now, look. Cookie, I'm lost.

325
00:44:48,018 --> 00:44:51,977
Do you know Campos St. Bonavus?
Yes.

326
00:44:52,189 --> 00:44:57,650
You take me there. Ok?
Yes, Miss.

327
00:44:59,763 --> 00:45:07,226
I wash face. You want to wash face?
Ok. I'll wash my face, too.

328
00:45:09,740 --> 00:45:12,573
Wonderful!

329
00:45:12,776 --> 00:45:16,735
C'mon. Iet's go.

330
00:45:44,374 --> 00:45:47,468
Your legs gone, lady?

331
00:45:47,678 --> 00:45:53,583
You say the cuttest things.

332
00:45:54,017 --> 00:45:59,319
Look, take that and that. All that.
And you stay here.

333
00:45:59,523 --> 00:46:02,492
Ok.

334
00:46:18,242 --> 00:46:23,145
Very difficult for ladies.

335
00:46:23,347 --> 00:46:26,180
I'm now going to take a picture.

336
00:46:26,383 --> 00:46:30,843
Okey-doke.
Okey-doke. That's about it.

337
00:46:35,793 --> 00:46:41,254
You're in the way.
You don't want my picture, lady?

338
00:46:44,835 --> 00:46:47,303
What's it for?

339
00:46:48,172 --> 00:46:50,732
I'm trying to
take the picture of that shop.

340
00:46:50,941 --> 00:46:53,307
Sometimes, I think you're very peculiar.

341
00:46:53,510 --> 00:46:56,968
Thanks, cookie.

342
00:46:57,181 --> 00:47:00,150
Ok. Shoot.

343
00:47:00,417 --> 00:47:02,442
Look. Coming here.

344
00:47:02,653 --> 00:47:06,089
Be a good boy. Stand over there.
Don't move and shut up.

345
00:47:06,290 --> 00:47:11,250
Go ahead. Now. Stop. Ok.

346
00:47:58,208 --> 00:48:03,077
You should've seen me in the Olympics.

347
00:48:03,280 --> 00:48:06,249
Skip it.

348
00:48:24,034 --> 00:48:27,003
Mauro! Mauro!

349
00:48:27,304 --> 00:48:30,171
Here, lady.
Take me home.

350
00:48:30,374 --> 00:48:33,343
Ok, lady.

351
00:49:12,983 --> 00:49:17,181
Good afternoon. How are you?
Not so bad. I fell into the canal.

352
00:49:18,055 --> 00:49:20,250
Oh yes, I'm so sorry.

353
00:49:20,457 --> 00:49:22,516
You played hooky this afternoon.
I played hooky?

354
00:49:24,394 --> 00:49:26,760
I was at your shop.
Didn't the boy tell you?

355
00:49:26,964 --> 00:49:29,398
Yes. Yes.
He is very kind.

356
00:49:29,599 --> 00:49:31,226
He is my niece.
Nephew.

357
00:49:31,435 --> 00:49:36,065
Nephew. Of course. Just when I think
I speak English like the

358
00:49:36,273 --> 00:49:38,639
American, something happens.

359
00:49:38,842 --> 00:49:41,743
Anyhow, he is the son of my eldest sister.

360
00:49:41,945 --> 00:49:49,408
Bravo! That about concludes
my entire performance in ltalian.

361
00:49:53,223 --> 00:49:56,386
Should I call somebody for you?

362
00:49:56,593 --> 00:50:00,586
Who?
I don't know. Mrs. Fiorini?

363
00:50:00,797 --> 00:50:03,698
I scarcely know her.

364
00:50:03,900 --> 00:50:07,631
Do you want to go somewhere?
No.

365
00:50:07,838 --> 00:50:11,797
I came to see you.

366
00:50:12,843 --> 00:50:18,213
Oh, you found another goblet.
No. Unfortunately, no.

367
00:50:18,415 --> 00:50:23,409
There are not many old goblets
in Venice any more. But we'll look.

368
00:50:23,620 --> 00:50:30,082
Don't go for any trouble.
For you? It is no trouble.

369
00:50:31,194 --> 00:50:34,163
May we go in?

370
00:50:34,631 --> 00:50:37,600
Sure.

371
00:50:47,978 --> 00:50:52,381
It's very hot.
Yes.

372
00:50:58,088 --> 00:51:03,025
That's better, isn't it?
Mr. Rossi, why did you come to see me?

373
00:51:03,226 --> 00:51:05,217
It is of nature.

374
00:51:05,429 --> 00:51:08,921
You don't give up something you like.
No.

375
00:51:09,132 --> 00:51:11,965
So I came.
Why?

376
00:51:12,169 --> 00:51:15,605
Does it matter why? You knew I would.

377
00:51:15,806 --> 00:51:18,434
I did not.

378
00:51:18,642 --> 00:51:21,634
How can I explain?
May be it's my English.

379
00:51:21,845 --> 00:51:24,245
May be it's mine.

380
00:51:24,448 --> 00:51:29,545
Listen. Two nights ago I went to
Piazza St. Marco. You were there.

381
00:51:29,753 --> 00:51:33,086
We looked. Next day, you were in my shop.

382
00:51:33,290 --> 00:51:36,453
We talked about glasses.
We talked about Venice.

383
00:51:36,660 --> 00:51:40,528
But we were not speak about that. Are we?

384
00:51:40,730 --> 00:51:47,465
So last night I was in St.Marco again.
You were at St. Marco again.

385
00:51:47,671 --> 00:51:51,004
Half of Venice are at St. Marco again.

386
00:51:51,208 --> 00:51:55,838
But half of Venice are not in my shop,
or I'll be a rich man.

387
00:51:56,046 --> 00:52:00,380
I wanted to buy another glass.
That's all

388
00:52:00,584 --> 00:52:02,609
There are shops all over Venice.

389
00:52:02,819 --> 00:52:06,983
Did you looking
at any of them for your glass?

390
00:52:07,190 --> 00:52:09,420
No.
You see?

391
00:52:09,626 --> 00:52:12,493
But you said you'll find one for me.

392
00:52:12,696 --> 00:52:15,460
That's why you came back?
Yes.

393
00:52:15,665 --> 00:52:19,066
Not that reason.

394
00:52:19,269 --> 00:52:23,831
I don't know what your experience
has been with American tourists.

395
00:52:24,040 --> 00:52:29,103
My experience has been that
tourist have more experience than l.

396
00:52:29,312 --> 00:52:32,907
Can we sit down?
No.

397
00:52:33,116 --> 00:52:34,913
I've offended you?

398
00:52:35,118 --> 00:52:37,916
Oh, yes. You're sorry I'm here.

399
00:52:38,121 --> 00:52:40,419
Then you're glad?

400
00:52:40,624 --> 00:52:46,893
It may be so to you, but I'm not
an ltalian. I'm an American,

401
00:52:47,097 --> 00:52:49,429
I thought everything
happens so fast in America.

402
00:52:49,633 --> 00:52:53,194
Not this sort of thing. Not to me.

403
00:52:53,403 --> 00:52:56,770
Yes. I have offended you.

404
00:52:56,973 --> 00:53:02,172
Mr. Rossi, I'm not a child.
But I don't understand.

405
00:53:02,379 --> 00:53:07,043
Understand? Why must you understand?

406
00:53:07,250 --> 00:53:11,243
The most beautiful things
in life are those we don't understand.

407
00:53:11,454 --> 00:53:16,187
As we spoke yesterday,
I knew you're simpatico.

408
00:53:16,393 --> 00:53:19,191
Is that something you understand?

409
00:53:19,396 --> 00:53:21,990
Yes, it means I'm like a sister to you.

410
00:53:22,199 --> 00:53:26,533
I have four sisters
and I'm not looking for another.

411
00:53:26,736 --> 00:53:31,332
Stop. You can make a joke.

412
00:53:31,541 --> 00:53:39,004
You make many jokes but inside.
I think you can.

413
00:53:41,551 --> 00:53:47,512
That's why you're simpatico.

414
00:53:53,897 --> 00:53:58,357
Miss. Hudson,
you ask me why I came to see you.

415
00:53:59,603 --> 00:54:03,801
Because you attract me. Why?

416
00:54:04,007 --> 00:54:07,033
Because you do.

417
00:54:07,244 --> 00:54:11,704
You Americans
are even more suspicious than French.

418
00:54:12,215 --> 00:54:18,484
Listen. We saw each other.
We like each other.

419
00:54:18,688 --> 00:54:21,521
This is so nice.

420
00:54:21,725 --> 00:54:25,684
How can it be wrong?

421
00:54:29,432 --> 00:54:34,995
Would you do me the honor
of seeing me this evening?

422
00:54:35,205 --> 00:54:38,766
Hello! Miss. Hudson. What a day we have.

423
00:54:38,975 --> 00:54:41,773
We've been shopping.
No, let them guess.

424
00:54:41,978 --> 00:54:46,210
This is Mr. Rossi.
Mr. and Mrs. Mcllenny.

425
00:54:46,416 --> 00:54:50,785
How are you?
Fine, thank you.

426
00:54:50,987 --> 00:54:54,150
It's so nice to be ltalian in ltaly.

427
00:54:54,357 --> 00:54:57,520
Glad to know you, Mr. Rossi.
How do you do?

428
00:54:57,727 --> 00:55:00,321
It's hot. I guess
we kind of overrun our schedule.

429
00:55:00,530 --> 00:55:03,693
What did you buy?
Glass, glass and more glass.

430
00:55:03,900 --> 00:55:04,992
She even sent home a chandelier.

431
00:55:05,201 --> 00:55:07,897
And before that, we did
the glass factory, picture gallery, the

432
00:55:08,104 --> 00:55:13,064
whole works. The pictures were marvelous
you tell them.

433
00:55:13,276 --> 00:55:15,574
Yes, she is right.
That place certainly sold me art.

434
00:55:15,779 --> 00:55:17,542
It gotta be fine art.
Oh, yes.

435
00:55:17,747 --> 00:55:21,513
That you gotta see, Miss. Hudson.
Come rain or snow, you gotta see.

436
00:55:21,718 --> 00:55:24,687
Oh boy, pictures. Rooms full of pictures.

437
00:55:24,888 --> 00:55:27,789
Hundreds of pictures. All done by hand.

438
00:55:27,991 --> 00:55:32,519
And the cuttest glass.
C'mon, I just gotta show you.

439
00:55:32,729 --> 00:55:34,754
Over there, so pretty, Lloyd.

440
00:55:34,964 --> 00:55:37,159
What are they?
Benetian glass.

441
00:55:37,367 --> 00:55:41,667
Please don't bother to unwrap it.
It'no bother. I'll show you one.

442
00:55:41,871 --> 00:55:45,500
And you gotta do this please.
You stand right there and watch them

443
00:55:45,709 --> 00:55:49,475
They put this stuff on long poles
and they heat it to the furnace.

444
00:55:49,679 --> 00:55:54,412
And presto change glass! And such colors.

445
00:55:54,617 --> 00:55:59,316
You have no idea. There!

446
00:55:59,522 --> 00:56:03,481
Isn't that exquisite?

447
00:56:03,727 --> 00:56:05,854
Stunning!

448
00:56:06,062 --> 00:56:09,657
Oddly enough.
I was looking for one just like it.

449
00:56:09,866 --> 00:56:11,891
They're only too
happy to make them for you.

450
00:56:12,102 --> 00:56:14,593
I bought half a dozen.

451
00:56:14,804 --> 00:56:17,102
They practically making them
for you while you stand there.

452
00:56:17,307 --> 00:56:18,831
If I may ask, how much did you pay?

453
00:56:19,042 --> 00:56:21,636
Not too much.
Lloyd, honestly.

454
00:56:21,845 --> 00:56:24,678
You know they wanted 1 1,500 lira a piece
But you never give them

455
00:56:24,881 --> 00:56:26,712
what they want.

456
00:56:26,916 --> 00:56:29,646
You just beat them down every time....

457
00:56:29,853 --> 00:56:34,620
I'm terribly sorry.
No, ltalians love to bargain.

458
00:56:34,824 --> 00:56:37,054
How much did you pay finally?

459
00:56:37,260 --> 00:56:40,229
Well, 1 0,000.

460
00:56:40,530 --> 00:56:42,122
It's fair.

461
00:56:42,332 --> 00:56:46,132
Oh we missed something.
We never got around the National Library.

462
00:56:46,336 --> 00:56:51,638
We can get that over with
in morning before we catch the train.

463
00:56:51,841 --> 00:56:59,304
Sometimes I think the schedule
in Venice is just, well, all wrong.

464
00:56:59,816 --> 00:57:03,946
There you go.
Why! Thank you.

465
00:57:04,154 --> 00:57:07,123
(ltalian)

466
00:57:17,500 --> 00:57:23,837
I know a little shop where
Mrs. Mcllenny could've saved 7,800 lira.

467
00:57:24,040 --> 00:57:26,531
I didn't say
your glass which was made yesterday.

468
00:57:26,743 --> 00:57:29,803
Of course not. It was 1 8 century, cookie.

469
00:57:30,013 --> 00:57:30,945
Do not call me cookie.

470
00:57:31,147 --> 00:57:33,945
It's politer than some
other names that come to mind.

471
00:57:34,150 --> 00:57:35,447
Now you're angry.
No.

472
00:57:35,652 --> 00:57:38,985
Suspicious again.
Angry, no. Suspicious, yes.

473
00:57:39,189 --> 00:57:41,054
You can always
find something to be suspicious of.

474
00:57:41,257 --> 00:57:43,122
Well I can and this doesn't help.
Suspicious.....

475
00:57:43,326 --> 00:57:49,287
What do you want me to do?

476
00:57:49,599 --> 00:57:52,067
Benetian glass
the same design used over and over

477
00:57:52,268 --> 00:57:53,758
for years and years.

478
00:57:53,970 --> 00:57:56,461
Your goblet is aging centuries.

479
00:57:56,673 --> 00:58:02,634
You can't believe me, you're not.

480
00:58:05,615 --> 00:58:09,073
Now please, believe me.

481
00:58:09,285 --> 00:58:14,587
If you do me the honor
of taking confidant tonight?

482
00:58:14,791 --> 00:58:18,921
There is a concert tonight.

483
00:58:19,128 --> 00:58:22,120
Would you like to go?

484
00:58:22,332 --> 00:58:28,293
He is beginning music with someone.

485
00:58:29,305 --> 00:58:31,398
Relax.

486
00:58:31,608 --> 00:58:34,771
Relax and the world is beautiful.

487
00:58:34,978 --> 00:58:38,937
Take a deep breath.

