00:58:41,351 --> 00:58:44,320
There.

489
00:58:45,822 --> 00:58:48,985
There is not very much
to have confidence in me, is it?

490
00:58:49,192 --> 00:58:53,595
No.
What happens after that.....happens.

491
00:58:54,931 --> 00:58:58,890
Does not happen.

492
01:00:35,665 --> 01:00:38,634
This is all and
more than I ever dreamed of.

493
01:00:38,835 --> 01:00:41,497
Back in Akron.

494
01:00:41,704 --> 01:00:43,729
You're a surprising person.

495
01:00:43,940 --> 01:00:46,408
Surprising?
Uh-hum.

496
01:00:46,609 --> 01:00:49,840
Every woman should
surprise a man at least once

497
01:00:50,046 --> 01:00:52,310
How many times have I surprised you?

498
01:00:52,515 --> 01:00:55,279
I think you surprise me all the time.

499
01:00:55,485 --> 01:01:02,550
Sometimes, you surprise me.
Pleasantly?

500
01:01:02,759 --> 01:01:07,219
Well....
Here is, to many pleasant surprises.

501
01:01:24,714 --> 01:01:29,777
Which flower do you prefer?

502
01:01:29,986 --> 01:01:32,386
Which one do you think I should have?

503
01:01:32,588 --> 01:01:35,614
Choose.
I think I know which one you choose

504
01:01:35,825 --> 01:01:39,056
You do? Perhaps I might surprise you.

505
01:01:39,262 --> 01:01:42,060
Perhaps. Choose.

506
01:01:42,265 --> 01:01:45,234
Perhaps not.

507
01:01:47,470 --> 01:01:50,962
Surprised?
I'm afraid so.

508
01:01:51,174 --> 01:01:54,143
Thank you.

509
01:01:57,814 --> 01:01:59,475
Which flower
did you think I would choose?

510
01:01:59,682 --> 01:02:06,144
The rose? the carnation?
Oh, dear, I should've known.

511
01:02:07,690 --> 01:02:10,090
For once, I wasn't the touring American.

512
01:02:10,293 --> 01:02:13,285
Why did you choose that flower?

513
01:02:13,496 --> 01:02:16,897
I once went to a ball.

514
01:02:17,100 --> 01:02:21,002
Not just the ordinary dance,
but a real ball.

515
01:02:21,204 --> 01:02:24,173
It was the first one I ever been to.

516
01:02:24,373 --> 01:02:29,276
Somehow, I got it into my mind
that I had to wear gardenia.

517
01:02:29,479 --> 01:02:31,208
I don't know why.

518
01:02:31,414 --> 01:02:34,110
I guess I read about
gardenia in a book or something.

519
01:02:34,317 --> 01:02:36,285
I must have it.
I didn't even know what to wear.

520
01:02:36,486 --> 01:02:39,819
Did you wear one?

521
01:02:40,022 --> 01:02:44,425
Gardenias turned out
to cost two dollars a piece.

522
01:02:44,627 --> 01:02:48,290
And the boy I was
going with was still in college.

523
01:02:48,498 --> 01:02:51,467
It was nice theme.

524
01:02:51,667 --> 01:02:55,603
Well, now you have your gardenia.

525
01:02:55,805 --> 01:02:58,774
Yes.

526
01:03:00,409 --> 01:03:06,370
Everything happens sooner or later.

527
01:03:07,116 --> 01:03:12,315
Yes. That's what they say.

528
01:03:12,522 --> 01:03:18,483
Everything happens to him who waits.

529
01:03:23,065 --> 01:03:28,526
Let's take a walk.
Alright.

530
01:03:56,399 --> 01:03:57,991
That's where I was born.

531
01:03:58,034 --> 01:04:00,935
You see the window?
With a basket of flowers?

532
01:04:01,137 --> 01:04:05,471
Oh, yes.
Sixty four steps up. I used to count them.

533
01:04:05,875 --> 01:04:07,240
That was a lot of steps.

534
01:04:07,877 --> 01:04:12,337
It's still is.
I went back there a year ago.

535
01:04:34,036 --> 01:04:36,596
What are they doing?
Is it a festival or something?

536
01:04:36,806 --> 01:04:39,297
No. They're just having fun.

537
01:04:39,508 --> 01:04:43,239
They'll have supper somewhere
on the canal. They'll sing songs.

538
01:04:43,446 --> 01:04:50,852
Look the stars, and perhaps,
Well, it is dark on the canal.

539
01:04:57,827 --> 01:05:05,290
I'll catch it from the steps.
It doesn't matter.

540
01:05:31,894 --> 01:05:34,863
Oh, Renato!

541
01:05:48,277 --> 01:05:51,178
You're home.

542
01:05:54,951 --> 01:05:58,011
Say it again.
Say what?

543
01:05:58,220 --> 01:06:01,189
My name.

544
01:06:07,897 --> 01:06:09,159
Why did you do that?

545
01:06:09,365 --> 01:06:12,630
Why!
Yes. Why did you do that? Like that.

546
01:06:12,835 --> 01:06:14,063
I don't think I want to see you again.

547
01:06:14,270 --> 01:06:18,730
You don't?
Oh, but l......

548
01:06:25,514 --> 01:06:28,483
I love you.

549
01:06:30,119 --> 01:06:34,579
Tomorrow.
Eight.

550
01:07:14,663 --> 01:07:17,632
Hey! Lady.

551
01:07:19,502 --> 01:07:24,030
You're supposed to
come this morning. Remember?

552
01:07:24,240 --> 01:07:27,732
I'm sorry. I'm very, very sorry.

553
01:07:27,943 --> 01:07:33,404
If you're really sorry
you buy Swiss watch, 1 0 dollars.

554
01:07:35,551 --> 01:07:38,019
I must fly.
Where're you going?

555
01:07:38,220 --> 01:07:40,381
I have an appointment.

556
01:07:40,589 --> 01:07:44,355
Take my cordo. Lady.

557
01:07:44,560 --> 01:07:50,192
I must've forgotten that, too.

558
01:07:50,399 --> 01:07:53,368
Crazy!

559
01:08:37,880 --> 01:08:40,849
(ltalian)

560
01:08:43,419 --> 01:08:49,824
Do you really think so?
Yes, Yes.

561
01:09:23,192 --> 01:09:26,059
Miss. Hudson.
Oh, it's you.

562
01:09:26,262 --> 01:09:28,321
Good evening. I bring a message.

563
01:09:28,531 --> 01:09:30,021
Mr. Rossi can't make it.

564
01:09:30,232 --> 01:09:35,693
Oh no, he'll be here.
But he must be little late.

565
01:09:37,673 --> 01:09:39,732
It was very nice
of you to come and tell me.

566
01:09:39,942 --> 01:09:42,740
Not at all.
Won't you have some coffee?

567
01:09:42,945 --> 01:09:44,879
No, thank you.

568
01:09:45,080 --> 01:09:46,980
Please sit down.

569
01:09:47,183 --> 01:09:49,310
Thank you.

570
01:09:49,518 --> 01:09:51,611
Cigarette?
American?

571
01:09:51,820 --> 01:09:54,152
Yes.
Thank you.

572
01:09:54,356 --> 01:09:56,449
American cigarettes are marvelous.

573
01:09:56,659 --> 01:10:02,495
But I'll save it for later,
if you don't mind. Permit me.

574
01:10:02,698 --> 01:10:07,567
Do you like working for Mr. Rossi?
Very much.

575
01:10:07,770 --> 01:10:10,330
Do you think he is a nice man?

576
01:10:10,539 --> 01:10:15,306
Yes. He is great..Iike God, for you, too.

577
01:10:15,511 --> 01:10:19,607
You don't know how upset
he was when he knew you'd be late.

578
01:10:19,815 --> 01:10:24,275
He didn't want to be.
My youngest sister, she was little ill,

579
01:10:24,486 --> 01:10:28,115
It was nothing really,
he worries so much about the same thing.

580
01:10:28,324 --> 01:10:31,020
He does.
Always.

581
01:10:31,227 --> 01:10:33,525
He worries about whose children?

582
01:10:33,729 --> 01:10:38,189
His. Us.
Us? Who are us?

583
01:10:39,335 --> 01:10:43,294
I'm the oldest. Vito.

584
01:10:44,006 --> 01:10:47,305
And how is your mother?
Fine. Thank you.

585
01:10:47,509 --> 01:10:51,411
So am l. Except the hole in my head.

586
01:10:51,614 --> 01:10:53,241
Excuse me, please. My English is not....

587
01:10:53,449 --> 01:10:59,285
Sorry. I think you better
tell your father not to come.

588
01:10:59,488 --> 01:11:01,615
But it won't be long.
No, no, it's alright.

589
01:11:01,824 --> 01:11:03,189
Just tell him not to come.

590
01:11:03,392 --> 01:11:08,830
Perhaps I tell him tomorow night.
No. Thank you for your trouble.

591
01:11:09,031 --> 01:11:13,491
Good-by.
Good-by.

592
01:11:32,288 --> 01:11:34,848
Hello.

593
01:11:35,057 --> 01:11:38,026
Oh, hello.

594
01:11:38,894 --> 01:11:42,022
What's the matter with you?
Marriage troubles.

595
01:11:42,231 --> 01:11:45,598
I wish I had them. Matter of fact, I do.

596
01:11:45,801 --> 01:11:50,204
Here you go.
Thanks.

597
01:11:51,907 --> 01:11:56,367
Cry again.
You cry. I'm sunk.

598
01:11:56,712 --> 01:12:01,172
Not you.
Not me!? I'm feeling miserable.

599
01:12:02,818 --> 01:12:04,718
But everybody loves you.
I know.

600
01:12:04,920 --> 01:12:06,410
They do.
I don't want everybody.

601
01:12:06,622 --> 01:12:08,487
I can't handle the crowd.

602
01:12:08,691 --> 01:12:13,628
I can't even handle.....Here I go again.

603
01:12:13,829 --> 01:12:19,233
Everything goes crazy for me.
Everything always is crazy.

604
01:12:19,435 --> 01:12:22,529
I got to be everything.

605
01:12:22,738 --> 01:12:25,172
You got to be everything?
Is that crazy?

606
01:12:25,374 --> 01:12:30,641
Yeah, that's crazy. Two of you, cookie.

607
01:12:30,846 --> 01:12:33,474
What do you mean?
Two. That's lovely isn't......

608
01:12:33,682 --> 01:12:34,546
Don't push your luck too far.

609
01:12:34,750 --> 01:12:37,878
Everything doesn't go crazy,
you just ask too much.

610
01:12:38,087 --> 01:12:41,079
What's the matter? What did I say?

611
01:12:41,290 --> 01:12:45,784
Nothing. I'm teribly sorry.
Nothing. It's me.

612
01:12:45,994 --> 01:12:49,691
Something happened to you?
No, no, nothing happened to me.

613
01:12:49,898 --> 01:12:55,302
That's my history.
Have stale potato chips.

614
01:13:16,158 --> 01:13:22,563
Listen. I don't love you.
Who asked?

615
01:13:22,765 --> 01:13:28,704
It was very pleasant time we had.

616
01:13:29,138 --> 01:13:33,598
Mauro!
Gondola.

617
01:14:03,839 --> 01:14:05,397
Where did you get that for?
It's mine.

618
01:14:05,607 --> 01:14:07,905
Where did you get that for? That's dirty.

619
01:14:08,110 --> 01:14:10,840
I want it.
Is that what you do? Is that your work?

620
01:14:11,046 --> 01:14:16,450
What's matter? What's matter?
Stop that! you hear? You stop that!

621
01:14:16,652 --> 01:14:21,851
What did he do?
That was too...he is just a baby, a child.

622
01:14:22,057 --> 01:14:29,520
I thought you like the child.
What's matter? You crazy?

623
01:14:40,509 --> 01:14:42,807
Something happens to this city at night.

624
01:14:43,011 --> 01:14:45,275
Are you going to get away from Venice?

625
01:14:45,481 --> 01:14:49,110
Your friend with in Kansas City.
Not in a gondola.

626
01:14:49,318 --> 01:14:51,479
That's ungratitude Venice.

627
01:14:51,687 --> 01:14:54,451
Jane.
Don't call me Jane.

628
01:14:54,656 --> 01:14:56,317
Miss. Hudson, you're shocked.

629
01:14:56,525 --> 01:14:58,459
Disappointed.
No, shocked.

630
01:14:58,660 --> 01:14:58,955
I don't like dishonesty.
You're not his wife.

631
01:15:03,232 --> 01:15:06,929
Why didn't you tell me you're married?

632
01:15:07,135 --> 01:15:11,401
I see.
Why?

633
01:15:11,607 --> 01:15:13,268
Why?

634
01:15:13,475 --> 01:15:16,774
I was afraid.
I was afraid if you knew too soon,

635
01:15:16,979 --> 01:15:21,939
It'll end us before we begin.
Now, I'm afraid I was right.

636
01:15:22,184 --> 01:15:25,415
No wonder
you approve of that sort of thing.

637
01:15:25,621 --> 01:15:29,819
Approve?
What Ms. Fiorini does is not my business.

638
01:15:30,025 --> 01:15:32,823
She leaves, I leave. I approve of leaving

639
01:15:33,028 --> 01:15:35,053
Pretending everything is fine and dandy,

640
01:15:35,264 --> 01:15:37,095
Just because you want to do it.

641
01:15:37,299 --> 01:15:39,733
You Americans get so disturbed about sex.

642
01:15:39,935 --> 01:15:46,397
We don't take it lightly.
Take it, don't talk it.

643
01:15:48,810 --> 01:15:50,471
My wife and I don't live together.

644
01:15:50,679 --> 01:15:55,139
Why?
Why? It is an arrangement.

645
01:15:56,251 --> 01:15:58,947
Does your wife have friends?

646
01:15:59,154 --> 01:16:01,679
Naturally.
Gondola friends?

647
01:16:01,890 --> 01:16:03,858
No.

648
01:16:04,059 --> 01:16:05,549
You're shocked.
No. Disappointed.

649
01:16:05,761 --> 01:16:08,992
No. Shocked.
Your sense of humor is coming back. Good.

650
01:16:09,197 --> 01:16:11,961
I'm sorry, yours is leaving.
Listen to me. Stop.

651
01:16:12,167 --> 01:16:13,691
You behave like a schoolgirl.

652
01:16:13,902 --> 01:16:15,961
What my wife does
is none of your business.

653
01:16:16,171 --> 01:16:18,765
What Ms. Fiorini does
is none of your business.

654
01:16:18,974 --> 01:16:20,441
You come here and what you do?

655
01:16:20,642 --> 01:16:25,011
You ride in gondola,
Oh Venice, so beautiful, so romantic.

656
01:16:25,213 --> 01:16:28,410
Oh, these ltalians,
so lyrical, so romantic.

657
01:16:28,617 --> 01:16:35,022
You dream of meeting someone you want.
Young, rich, witty

658
01:16:35,257 --> 01:16:37,248
And unmarried, of course.

659
01:16:37,459 --> 01:16:43,193
But me, I'm a shopkeeper.
Not young. Not rich. Not witty

660
01:16:43,398 --> 01:16:46,367
And married, of course.

661
01:16:46,568 --> 01:16:50,732
I'm a man and you're a woman.

662
01:16:50,939 --> 01:16:56,571
Don't you see? It's wrong.
That's the way it is.

663
01:16:56,778 --> 01:17:00,714
You're like a hungry child.
Was given ravioli to eat.

664
01:17:00,949 --> 01:17:06,080
No, you say, I want beefsteak.

665
01:17:06,288 --> 01:17:13,751
My dear girl, you're hungry.
Eat that ravioli.

666
01:17:14,029 --> 01:17:19,490
I'm not that hungry.
We're all the time, Miss. Hudson.

667
01:17:21,703 --> 01:17:28,040
There is noise in your head.
Be quiet. Let it happen.

668
01:17:28,243 --> 01:17:30,677
I want it to happen.

669
01:17:30,879 --> 01:17:34,076
I want it to happen.
Don't you think I do?

670
01:17:34,282 --> 01:17:36,477
Then?
It's just.....

671
01:17:36,685 --> 01:17:41,349
Isn't the way I thought it would be.
I'm sorry.

672
01:17:41,556 --> 01:17:45,287
But l...come from
such a different world, and I'm not

673
01:17:45,494 --> 01:17:47,553
Going to be here long.

674
01:17:47,763 --> 01:17:53,167
So it is better
to take home when you have it.

675
01:18:04,613 --> 01:18:08,913
If you really not so hungry,
you do that very well.

676
01:18:09,117 --> 01:18:10,675
Do l?

677
01:18:10,886 --> 01:18:12,615
Yes.

678
01:18:12,821 --> 01:18:14,618
Let me take you outside.
No.

679
01:18:14,823 --> 01:18:19,283
Please.
No. I'm gonna go for a walk alone.

680
01:18:25,534 --> 01:18:28,970
Please leave me alone.

681
01:18:29,004 --> 01:18:32,940
It is very difficult.

682
01:18:33,875 --> 01:18:36,309
Let me take you to a drink.
No.

683
01:18:36,511 --> 01:18:42,746
At least something to eat.
No.

684
01:18:42,951 --> 01:18:50,357
There are fireworks tonight.
I don't care.

685
01:19:02,137 --> 01:19:05,129
This is ridiculous.

686
01:19:05,340 --> 01:19:09,276
I'm afraid it is.

687
01:19:11,880 --> 01:19:16,340
Gondola, sir?
No.

688
01:21:48,403 --> 01:21:51,702
Do you know the words?
Yes. This song says....

689
01:21:51,907 --> 01:21:54,273
I know what it says.

690
01:21:54,476 --> 01:22:00,381
Have you ever had it in America?
No.

691
01:22:00,582 --> 01:22:04,109
You sing it.
How do you know I can?

692
01:22:04,953 --> 01:22:09,890
Because you're ltalian.

693
01:25:35,130 --> 01:25:38,099
(ltalian)

694
01:26:36,791 --> 01:26:42,024
They call it Fangela Coppoli.
What does that mean?

695
01:26:42,230 --> 01:26:48,191
The island where the rainbow fell.

696
01:27:44,525 --> 01:27:49,462
It's very late. We ought to go.

697
01:27:49,697 --> 01:27:53,394
Are you asleep?
Fast asleep.

698
01:27:53,601 --> 01:27:57,367
You slept all day yesterday.
True

699
01:27:57,572 --> 01:28:03,010
You sleep all day and
you don't want to sleep at night.

700
01:28:08,583 --> 01:28:11,518
You promised to take me to see
sights and now it's too late.

701
01:28:11,719 --> 01:28:13,949
I'll take you tomorrow.

702
01:28:17,392 --> 01:28:21,852
You promise?
No.

703
01:28:23,131 --> 01:28:27,568
Now, do you promise?
It is difficult.

704
01:28:27,769 --> 01:28:31,227
If you don't, I'll never kiss you again.

705
01:28:31,472 --> 01:28:34,441
Yes, you will.

706
01:28:35,910 --> 01:28:39,846
Yes. I guess so.

707
01:29:49,016 --> 01:29:53,976
They're getting to know us.
You asked them to play it.

708
01:29:54,222 --> 01:29:57,191
I did.

709
01:30:42,503 --> 01:30:46,439
You're far away.

710
01:30:46,674 --> 01:30:50,576
I'm very close.

711
01:30:50,978 --> 01:30:54,914
What are you thinking?

712
01:30:56,350 --> 01:31:00,787
I was thinking
the first evening I came here.

713
01:31:03,491 --> 01:31:08,929
First time I saw you,
you were wearing that yellow tie.

714
01:31:11,966 --> 01:31:19,429
I don't want to forget any of it.
Not a single moment.

715
01:31:22,443 --> 01:31:28,382
I don't think I ever shall.

716
01:31:31,118 --> 01:31:35,817
I could go for a little walk.
Take us somewhere quiet.

717
01:31:36,023 --> 01:31:39,356
Somewhere that is you.

718
01:31:39,560 --> 01:31:45,499
I think you're going to surprise me again.

719
01:32:13,094 --> 01:32:18,794
Listen, Renato. I'm leaving today.

720
01:32:19,000 --> 01:32:23,198
I'm all packed.
My train leaves in two hours.

721
01:32:23,404 --> 01:32:26,032
I don't believe you.

722
01:32:26,240 --> 01:32:29,107
You have to believe me, because it's true.

723
01:32:29,310 --> 01:32:33,110
What have I done?

724
01:32:33,314 --> 01:32:35,646
Nothing.

725
01:32:35,850 --> 01:32:38,978
What made you change your mind?

726
01:32:39,186 --> 01:32:46,490
Well...I hadn't a mind change.
Really, I just found it.

727
01:32:46,694 --> 01:32:48,924
I haven't made you unhappy.

728
01:32:49,130 --> 01:32:53,829
No. You haven't. It's the happiest
time I had in my whole life.

729
01:32:54,035 --> 01:32:58,836
You must believe that, please.
Why throw it away?

730
01:32:59,040 --> 01:33:04,239
Because we have to. Because it's wrong.

731
01:33:04,445 --> 01:33:09,678
Because you and l
will only end in nothing.

732
01:33:09,884 --> 01:33:13,047
I love you, Jane.

733
01:33:13,254 --> 01:33:15,415
You don't have to say that.

734
01:33:15,623 --> 01:33:17,682
I mean it.

735
01:33:17,892 --> 01:33:20,656
I shall always love you.

736
01:33:20,861 --> 01:33:24,797
Yes. If I go.....

737
01:33:25,600 --> 01:33:28,194
All my life, I stayed
at parties too long, because

738
01:33:28,402 --> 01:33:31,030
I didn't know when to go.

739
01:33:31,238 --> 01:33:34,207
Now with you, I've grown up.

740
01:33:34,408 --> 01:33:37,172
I think I do know when to.

741
01:33:37,378 --> 01:33:41,872
I can't bear it if you go today.
I can't bear it, either.

742
01:33:42,083 --> 01:33:47,487
Just a few days.
No. I couldn't. Then I never go.

743
01:33:47,688 --> 01:33:53,593
Please. No. Take me to the station.

744
01:33:54,662 --> 01:34:00,623
Oh, no no, please. Please help me.

745
01:34:12,647 --> 01:34:18,085
Let me go by myself.
Don't go, please.

746
01:34:19,420 --> 01:34:23,356
Please don't go.

747
01:34:23,691 --> 01:34:26,660
Let me go.

748
01:34:28,696 --> 01:34:31,927
I must catch that train.
I'll take you to the station.

749
01:34:32,133 --> 01:34:35,466
No, that's just what
I don't want you to do.

750
01:34:35,670 --> 01:34:38,639
Oh, Renato.

751
01:35:34,328 --> 01:35:37,297
Mauro!

752
01:35:38,599 --> 01:35:39,691
What are you doing here?

753
01:35:39,900 --> 01:35:43,358
I come to say good-by.

754
01:35:43,604 --> 01:35:48,871
I'm sorry, Mauro, I'm very, very sorry.
Ok, ok.

755
01:35:49,076 --> 01:35:52,170
You going to Rome?
I'm going home.

756
01:35:52,379 --> 01:35:53,971
To America?
Yes.

757
01:35:54,181 --> 01:35:57,844
You come back again?
Yeah, yeah, sure.

758
01:35:58,052 --> 01:36:01,249
You come back with a big American man?

759
01:36:01,455 --> 01:36:04,618
I'll be your guide.
Ok.

760
01:36:04,825 --> 01:36:08,488
Want this?
No, thank you.

761
01:36:08,696 --> 01:36:14,635
It's not for sale. It's a present.

762
01:36:14,969 --> 01:36:19,406
Why?
Because I like you.

763
01:36:23,544 --> 01:36:26,911
You okey-doke, lady?
Sure, I'm okey-doke.

764
01:36:27,114 --> 01:36:31,574
Be seeing you.
Be seeing you.

765
01:36:41,929 --> 01:36:44,898
Thank you.

766
01:37:44,024 --> 01:37:46,993
Renato!

